</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 591<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/9/01 4:21:16 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/snchicktourney/larges/132.jpg width=130 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need opinions - Last Piece Rule</span><hr size=1> I think last piece rule should come into effect when someone is going to loot the last piece of armor that they will actually every wear.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
I have a BP that is 99% superior to RE BP.<br>
I have a pair of legs that is 99% superior to RE legs.<br>
I will never ever wear RE legs or BP.<br>
I would like to think that I could use the last piece rule in claiming a helmet if one dropped, since I'll never use the BP or legs, and someone else can loot them.<br>
<br>
There's many many items available now that are superior to planar armor.  Why subject someone to staying in the planes any longer than they want just because they only want to get 1 or 2 pieces from the plane.<br>
<br>
Back to your arguement, if someone doesn't want to loot a 2nd bracer, why are you forcing them to? <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>57 Halfling Shaman
<br><img src=http://www.tbp.mb.ca/~stimpy/everquest/JuujuuHalflingSentry.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukruuunch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kruuunch</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim</span><br>  Posts: 1649<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/9/01 6:24:01 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.krunch.net/kruunch-face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need opinions - Last Piece Rule</span><hr size=1> Last piece means LAST piece.<br>
